
This repository contains my **personal HTML notes**, created to document my learning journey and consolidate my conceptual understanding of HTML. 
The notes are intended to serve as a reference for myself and also to help others who are learning HTML, from basics to intermediate concepts. Note that these notes have been created
after learning from well know websites like geeks for geeks. Visit these webpages for a more detailed understanding of each concept.

## Purpose
- To **track and organize** my HTML learning progress.
- To provide **clear explanations** and examples for fundamental HTML concepts.
- To help **other learners** quickly understand HTML syntax, structure, and best practices.

## Content
The notes cover topics such as:  
- HTML structure and elements  
- Headings, paragraphs, and text formatting  
- Links, images, and multimedia  
- Lists, tables, and forms  
- Semantic HTML and accessibility  
- Basic styling and attributes  

## Learning Resources & References
concepts and explanations were reinforced using online resources such as:  
- [Apna College - YouTube Channel](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HcOc7P5BMi4&t=1008s)  
- [GeeksforGeeks](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/html/html-complete-guide/)  

## How to Use
- Browse through the notes to understand HTML concepts in a structured way.  
- Use examples to practice coding in your own HTML files.  
- Contributions or suggestions are welcome; feel free to open an issue or pull request if you have improvements or corrections.

## License
This repository is open for educational purposes. You may use the notes for personal learning and reference.

---

**Note:** These notes reflect my learning journey and conceptual understanding of HTML and are intended to assist both myself and fellow learners.

